Docs.summary: Enables the rule to apply to the application gateway's private (internal) frontend. If the private frontend IP configuration does not yet exist, it will be created under an auto-generated name. If the application gateway does not have a subnet specified for its private frontend, one will be created automatically, unless a specific subnet is specified in the application gateway definition's optional settings using {.

If the application gateway does not have a public IP address specified for its public frontend, one will be created automatically, unless a specific public IP address is specified in the application gateway definition's optional settings using {.
